The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Good Morning

 Hello It's Monday, January 2, 2006

 Dance show

 Performances by acrobats and dancers from Africa and Russia at Nicco Park, four shows every day.

 A programme based on creative dance, Bharatanatyam, kathak and kuchipudi, presented by Nupur Dance Troupe, at Swabhumi, 6 pm.

 Fashion

 Design?s annual silk sari exhibition at 108, Raja Basanta Roy Road, 11 am to 7.30 pm.

 Theatre

 Kananpishir Japmala will be staged, as part of Dwandwik Natyotsab, at Sarat Sadan, 6.30 pm.

 Fair

 The 5th Belghoria Utsav on Bhairab Ganguly College grounds.

 Exhibition

 Hastashilpa Unnayan Utsav, an exhibition of crafts, artefacts and other products made by rural artisans of Bengal, at Swabhumi Sabhaghar, noon to 8 pm.

 Futurestrokes, an exhibition of works by students of visual arts, at 2/1 Hindusthan Road, 11 am and 8 pm.

 Art watch

 Bengal pottery at Arts amp; Ideas, Swabhumi, noon to 8.30 pm.

 Works by graphic artist and director Enki Bilal at Victoria Memorial Hall.

 An exhibition celebrating the birth centenary of Abani Sen at Bharatiyam, 2 pm-7 pm.




